2017 WW12 Bakerville/SKX-D Silver Release Announcement (BKC #12)

\n \n \n

DEG Platform Integration Team

\n \n
\n

The DEG platform Integration team announces the release of 2017 WW12 Bakerville/SKX-D Silver release package for Intel internal use. The release is based on OS of\n \n ESXi6.5/\n \n RHEL7.3/\n \n WS2016\n server. The auto-installer packages are available in the Artifactory server (both SH site and OR site). Any questions please contact Bei, Ling.

Test Result:

l  Finish Silver test execution on RHEL 7.3 , Windows2016 and VMware ESXi6.5. Please visit HPQC for test details. Refer to the installation\nguide for the BKC package installation

l  Bakerville(RP Board: Yuba\nCity RP fab3)

o   Total test cases: 30; Passed test\ncases is 30 and pass rate is 100%. 

o   Test coverage:  

     SKX-D ES2\nSoC(QMXS, QMXT): Run\nP1 and P2 test cases on RHEL 7.3, Windows2016 and VMWare ESXi6.5; run Power & Performance test.

           SKX-D L0 VIS SoC: run power cycling test(G3/S5/warm-reboot)

HW rework:

    \n
  • No HW rework need for Yuba City\n fab3 board.
    • \n
  • jumper setting refers to\n this link.
    • \n

 Work\naround:

    \n
  • Secure Boot only can run in\n UEFI mode, so if we want secure boot can work and let bios load UEFI\n Oprom, we need Disable this option. 
    • \n

EDKII\nMenu -> Boot Options -> EFI INT10 workaround

    \n
  • When you flash onboard Aspeed\n BMC, in order to detect onboard dTPM in AC cycle, you need run below IPMI\n command in UEFI Shell:
    • \n
